This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a clustering technique for computer vision applications such as tracking, detection, and segmentation. The use of event-based sensors also suggests that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Kalman filters, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Finally, the paper's focus on real-time processing and optimization suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
